ust and Fountain of Life is pending. No criminal trial date has been set. Melonie Milling, Ms. <PERSON> Stevens </PERSON>' 27-year-old daughter, also lived in Mrs. Lust's home, investigators said. Ms. <PERSON> Stevens </PERSON> illegally obtained prescription drugs and gave them to Mrs. Lust to keep her sleepy so she would not complain, Ms. <PERSON> Milling </PERSON> told authorities. Ms. Milling also said her mother disconnected the telephone in the woman's bedroom and told her: `` See, no one cares, no one calls; your children do n't even call.'' Mrs. Lust, a paraplegic since suffering a stroke in 1982, also has impaired vision as a result of unsuccessful cataract surgery.
