<HEAD>With PM-Soviet Sub, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Soviet President <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> told Prime Minister <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> early today that the risk of explosion or contamination from a Soviet sub that sank off <LOCATION> Norway </LOCATION> was `` negligible,'' her office said. The Soviet leader also assured Mrs. <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> that the reactors on the nuclear-powered submarine had been shut down before the vessel caught fire and sank 312 miles off northern <LOCATION> Norway </LOCATION>, the prime minister's office said. <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> sent the message by telephone from his private office in <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> a few hours after he returned to <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> from a two-day visit to <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> where he held wide-ranging talks with Mrs. <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON>, her office said. Office staff at 10 Downing Street said it understood similar messages from <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON>'s office were sent to President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Norwegian </LOCATION> Prime Minister <PERSON> Gro </PERSON> <PERSON> Harlem </PERSON> <PERSON> Brundtland </PERSON>. The Soviet leader told Mrs. <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> that there had been loss of life but gave no figures, Downing Street said. Reports indicate at least 12 crew are dead of the estimated 95 crew that were on board the `` Mike'' class sub. In response, Mrs. <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON>'s office said it conveyed to <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> `` her condolences and sympathy for the families of those who lost their lives in the accident.'' The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> said today that the submarine sank in international waters 110 miles southwest of <LOCATION> Bear </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION> in the <LOCATION> Norwegian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sea </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Tass </ORGANIZATION> news agency said a rescue operation was u