CATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military presence in <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION>. Since 1982, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> have intensified military maneuvers provided for under a 1954 treaty. In the past nine years, more than 100,000 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> soldiers have come to <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> to train the 20,000-member Honduran armed forces.
