 </LOCATION> trade imbalance `` in the context of export expansion rather than import contraction. Under another agreement reached Saturday, delegates resolved <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> objections to earlier draft language that the 12-nation group said would remove textile and clothing barriers too rapidly. The agreement calls for further negotiations will be held later this month. Developing countries with large textile industries want liberal regulations. Industrialized countries such as the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> members are concerned about the impact a lack of restrictions might have on domestic industries.
