<HEAD>Exxon Dealers Sue Company, Say They're Cheated Out of Profits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An angry group of <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> service station owners filed suit against the oil giant, charging that <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION>'s manipulative practices take profits from dealers and saddle consumers with high fuel prices The 19 Exxon dealers, most from the <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> area, charged the nation's largest oil marketer with 15 counts of civil violations of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> antitrust and deceptive trade practices laws. The lawsuit was filed Friday in state district court. A spokesman for the dealers' group said the action was unrelated to the <LOCATION> Exxon </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valdez </LOCATION> oil disaster in <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION>. `` We finally had enough of it, and we're fighting back,'' said the spokesman, <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> dealer <PERSON> Clyde </PERSON> <PERSON> Hall </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Pasadena </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>. An <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> spokesman did not answer a telephone call from The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> on Saturday. The lawsuit seeks more than $ 5 million in actual damages and unspecified punitive damages. Hall and his fellow dealers complained that <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> favors select franchises with `` sweetheart'' rents, interferes with dealers' ability to buy gasoline cheaper from wholesalers and has rigid rules for the inheritance of dealers' stations when they die <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> is the second oil company sued by its dealers in the last six months. Last September, <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> was hit with a suit on a separate set of complaints by a band of dealer franchises in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> federal court. `` Is this the last of this type of suit you're going to see? No,'' said <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> <PERSON> Nilsson </PERSON>, executive director of the <ORG