N> <ORGANIZATION> Adviser </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brent </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Scowcroft </ORGANIZATION> and Deputy Security Adviser <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Gates </PERSON>, have been skeptical of some of the changes in the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>. But that approach has been criticized by some experts as too cautious at a time when the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> is undergoing monumental change that could dramatically alter American-Soviet relations, the Times reported. `` The real debate in the administration will be between the two centrist positions _ the stand-pat school and the seize-the-opportunity school,'' Rep. <PERSON> Les </PERSON> <PERSON> Aspin </PERSON>, D-Wis., told the Times The report to the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> suggested that the president could pursue dialogue for the two superpowers to combat terrorism jointly and slow the spread of chemical weapons, the Times said.
